<subSubSection id="253BA7BA0E8E634E38DA52CF4657F86D" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="297FC82575C50C306A667A574CF7734C" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="540AF7741042A9D0BAEA43E963E4BC73" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">The name is taken from the famous Jinding Scenic Spot, which is very close to Tupingao area in the Wugong Mountain National Forest Park; noun in apposition.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A930A505306801363B78B86A08BF6737" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A57F8C983D59463D40B9AAAB5A89823C" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3AEAF76A945A9C2395F3599CA9499A1D" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
The male of this species is most similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="981FCE22EE09603DCFAF4E578A9688C3" authorityName="Bohdanowicz" authorityYear="1979" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Synagelides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Synagelides annae" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annae">
<emphasis id="127DC9CD17B023FBCD33F45E5A467F58" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Synagelides annae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bohdanowicz, 1979 (see 
<bibRefCitation id="6044015B7E8F663BD12EC45D49B50641" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2476/asjaa.28.53" author="Bohdanowicz, A" journalOrPublisher="Acta Arachnologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" pagination="53 - 62" refId="B1" refString="Bohdanowicz, A, 1979. Descriptions of spiders of the genus Synagelides (Araneae: Salticidae) from Japan and Nepal. Acta Arachnologica 28 (2): 53 - 62, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2476/asjaa.28.53" title="Descriptions of spiders of the genus Synagelides (Araneae: Salticidae) from Japan and Nepal." url="https://doi.org/10.2476/asjaa.28.53" volume="28" year="1979">Bohdanowicz 1979</bibRefCitation>
: 56, figs 14-17) in having a sharp ventral femoral apophysis, an anticlockwise spiral embolus, a C-shaped terminal apophysis with hook-shaped tip, and the mastoid tegular apophysis in retrolateral view, but differs from it in having (Figs 
<figureCitation id="E550D403B2CC9C7F59FAB3F2C713E72E" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Synagelides jinding sp. nov., holotype male A habitus, dorsal view B same, ventral view C palp, prolateral view D same, ventral view E same, retrolateral view F same, detail of ventral femoral apophysis, retrolateral view G same, retrolateral view, slightly dorsal H same, dorsal view. Abbreviations: DTA - dorso-prolateral tibial apophysis, Em - embolus, PCA - postero-prolateral cymbial apophysis, RCA - postero-retrolateral cymbial apophysis, RTA - retrolateral tibial apophysis, SD - sperm duct, SS - scale-like serrations, TA - terminal apophysis, VFA - ventral femoral apophysis. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A, B); 0.05 mm (C-E, G, H); 0.1 mm (F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.76800.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686164" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">4C-H</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="18C876ECBFFC5F4643932250D5740DF8" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Synagelides jinding sp. nov., SEMs of holotype male A palp, ventral view B same, detail of terminal apophysis and embolus, ventral view C same, retrolateral view D same, detail of retrolateral tibial apophysis, retrolateral view E same, detail of terminal apophysis and embolus, retrolateral view F same, dorsal view, slightly prolateral G same, detail of postero-prolateral cymbial apophysis, postero-retrolateral cymbial apophysis and dorso-prolateral tibial apophysis, dorsal view. Abbreviations: DTA - dorso-prolateral tibial apophysis, Em - embolus, PCA - postero-prolateral cymbial apophysis, RCA - postero-retrolateral cymbial apophysis, RTA - retrolateral tibial apophysis, SS - scale-like serrations, TA - terminal apophysis." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.76800.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686165" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">5</figureCitation>
) the posterior cymbium with a long blunt retrolateral apophysis (vs absent), the parallel retrolateral tibial apophysis together with postero-retrolateral cymbial apophysis in retrolateral view (vs. convergent) and thick clavate retrolateral tibial apophysis (vs spine-like) with many scale-like serrations (vs absent). It also resembles those seven species 
<taxonomicName id="5DFF7FEEB8FC900633FA93437762A34A" genus="S." lsidName="S. birmanicus" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="birmanicus">
<emphasis id="8D4AE50FEACD8CF419C1FCC5B98A92D7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">S. birmanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bohdanowicz, 1987 (see 
<bibRefCitation id="C66E52BE582960988A9FF8ED23C5F086" author="Bohdanowicz, A" journalOrPublisher="Courier Forschungsinstitut Senckenberg" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" pagination="65 - 86" refId="B2" refString="Bohdanowicz, A, 1987. Salticidae from the Nepal Himalayas: The genus Synagelides Boesenberg &amp; Strand 1906. Courier Forschungsinstitut Senckenberg 93: 65 - 86" title="Salticidae from the Nepal Himalayas: The genus Synagelides Boesenberg &amp; Strand 1906." volume="93" year="1987">Bohdanowicz 1987</bibRefCitation>
: 84, figs 66-72), 
<taxonomicName id="460116BD9DF0D2C4B5F5AA8CD1978853" genus="S." lsidName="S. cavaleriei" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="cavaleriei">
<emphasis id="BF29391CB7283F65A33F52C47B8004C8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">S. cavaleriei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Schenkel, 1963) (see 
<bibRefCitation id="FA9D72318B623F328B4513FBFDEE45AF" author="Bohdanowicz, A" journalOrPublisher="Courier Forschungsinstitut Senckenberg" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" pagination="65 - 86" refId="B2" refString="Bohdanowicz, A, 1987. Salticidae from the Nepal Himalayas: The genus Synagelides Boesenberg &amp; Strand 1906. Courier Forschungsinstitut Senckenberg 93: 65 - 86" title="Salticidae from the Nepal Himalayas: The genus Synagelides Boesenberg &amp; Strand 1906." volume="93" year="1987">Bohdanowicz 1987</bibRefCitation>
: 66, figs 1, 2), 
<taxonomicName id="730EFE214CDE6831533EFC6FF50A5135" genus="S." lsidName="S. gosainkundicus" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="gosainkundicus">
<emphasis id="2FCE4949C5287A0B004EDA13A0746C01" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">S. gosainkundicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bohdanowicz, 1987 (see 
